{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Center loss, while promoting intra-class compactness and consequently aiding in inter-class separation, may still permit overlap among feature regions in the embedding space.",
    "Building on this concept, Cai et al. [11] enhanced center loss by integrating an additional objective function.",
    "This modified center loss, termed as island loss, merges the original center loss with the pairwise cosine distance between class centers in the embedding space.",
    "The approach aims to increase cosine distance, thereby angularly separating the class centers.",
    "Island loss has been assessed using datasets including CK+, MMI, and Oulu-CASI."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Building on this concept, Cai et al. [11] enhanced center loss by integrating an additional objective function."
  ]
}